    {
      "ESSeqNum": 0,
      "FacilityID": 1000076305,
      "SummaryText": "1. FACILITY ACCIDENTAL RELEASE AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE POLICY.\n\nTHE MANAGEMET AND EMPLOYEES OF ST CLAIR SERVICE COMPANY ARE COMMITTED TO THE PREVENTION OF ANY ACCIDENTAL RELEASES OF ANHYDROUS AMMONIA.  IF AN ACCIDENTIAL RELEASE SHOULD OCCUR, THE FACILITY IS PREPARED TO WORK WITH THE LOCAL FIRE DEPARTMENT, OR OTHER AUTHORITIES, TO MITIGATE ANY RELEASE AND MINIMIZE THE IMPACT OF THE RELEASE TO PEOPLE AND THE ENVIRONMENT.\n\n\n\n2. THE STATIONARY SOURCE AND THE REGULATED SUBSTANCES HANDLED.\n\nTHE PRIMARY ACTIVITY AT THE FACILITY LOCATED AT 1036 S. GREEN MOUNT RD, IS THE STORAGE AND BLENDING OF FERTILIZERS FOR SALE TO FARMERS.  ANHYDROUS AMMONIA IS RECEIVED, STORED, AND DISTRIBUTED FOR DIRECT APPLICATION AS A CROP PRODUCTION NUTRIENT.  ACCESS TO THE SITE IS RESTRICTED TO AUTHORIZED FACILITY EMPLOYEES, AUTHORIZED MANAGEMENT PERSONNEL AND AUTHORIZED CONTRACTORS.\n\n\n\n3. THE WORST-CASE RELEASE SCENARIO AND THE ALTERNATIVE RELEASE SCENARIO.\n\nTHIS FACILITY HAS DEVELOPED A WORST-CASE AND ALTERNATIVE-CASE SCENARIO, HOWEVER, SINCE THIS IS SECURITY-SENSITIVE INFORMATION IT HAS BEEN WITHHELD FROM THIS EXECUTIVE'S SUMMARY AS REQUIRED BY EPA REGULATIONS.\n\n\n\n4. THE ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM.\n\nTHIS FACILITY COMPLIES WITH EPA'S ACCIDENTAL PREVENTION RULE AND WITH ALL APPLICABLE STATE CODES AND REGULATIONS.  THIS FACILITY HAS IMPLEMENTED THE PROVISIONS OF \"SAFETY REQUIREMENTS FOR THE STORAGE AND HANDLING OF ANHYDROUS AMMONIA, K-61.1\" PUBLISHED BY THE AMERICAN NATIONAL STANDARDS INSTITUTE, INC.  AS ADOPTED BY STATE REGULATION AND THE STANDARDS OF THE U.S. OCCUPATIONAL SAFETY AND HEALTH ADMINISTRATION (OSHA), 29 CFR 1910.111, \"STORAGE AND HANDLING OF ANHYDROUS AMMONIA\". COMPLIANCE WITH THESE REGULATIONS AND ON-GOING TRAINING OF OUR EMPLOYEES MAKE UP OUR ACCIDENT RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM.\n\n\n\n5. FIVE YEAR ACCIDENT HISTORY.\n\nTHERE HAVE BEEN NO ACCIDENTAL RELEASES OF ANHYDROUS AMMONIA IN THE PAST FIVE YEARS THAT HAVE CAUSED ANY DEATHS, INJURIES, OR SIGNIFICANT PROPERTY DAMAGE AT THE FA"
    },
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 1,
      "FacilityID": 1000076305,
      "SummaryText": "CILITY: NOR TO OUR KNOWLEDGE, HAVE RESULTED IN OFFSITE DEATHS, INJURIES, EVACUATIONS, SHELTER IN PLACE, PROPERTY DAMAGE, OR ENVIRONMENTAL DAMAGE.\n\n\n\n6. THE EMERGENCY RESPONSE PROGRAM.\n\nTHE FACILITY HAS A WRITTEN EMERGENCY ACTION PLAN, IN ACCORDANCE WITH OSHA STANDARD,29 CFR 1910.38: PROVIDED THE STATE AND LOCAL AUTHORITIES THE EMERGENCY PLANNING AND THE COMMUNITY RIGHT-TO-KNOW INFORMATION AS REQUIRED UNDER SARA TITLE III (EPCRA); IN THE EVENT OF AN EMERGENCY INVOLVING ANHYDROUS AMMONIA, IT IS OUR POLICY TO NOTIFY THE LOCAL FIRE DEPARTMENT AND OTHER AUTHORITIES AND REQUEST THAT THEY RESPOND TO THE EMERGENCY. OUR EMERGENCY ACTION PLANS HAVE BEEN COORDINATED WITH BOTH THE FIRE DEPARTMENT AND LEPC.\n\n\n\n7. PLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY.\n\nSAFETY IMPROVEMENT IS AN ON-GOING PROCESS AT THE FACILITY.  PERIODIC EVALUATIONS ARE PERFORMED TO ASSESS THE MAINTENANCE OF SAFE CONDITIONS.  IN 2019 WE PLAN TO DO EXTENSIVE MAINTENCE AND UPGRADE THE FACILITY TO MEET NEW UPCOMING STATE REGULATIONS FOR THE HANDLING AND STORAGE OF ANHYDROUS AMMONIA.\n\n"
    }
